long_desc.thetext:
Right now we can only set one error handler on qx.event.GlobalError.

To handle different error types a lot of if-statements have to be written, e.g.

if (exc instanceof ErrorA) {
// do something
} else if (exc instanceof ErrorB) {
// do something
} else if...

It would be nice to have a registry for custom error handlers, e.g.:

addErrorHandler(ErrorA, handlerA, this);
addErrorHandler(ErrorB, handlerB, this);
...

Benefit:

* Clear API - usage of global error handler is more explicit.
* Custom error handlers can be reused (e.g. IO Error Handler, with status codes)
